pullRequest.body:
In this PR, we obtain the lemma `GradedObject.mapBifunctor_triangle` which promotes a triangle identity involving functors to a triangle identity for the induced functors on graded objects. More simp lemmas for isomorphisms like `Iso.map_hom_inv_id_eval_app ` are also added in order to ease automation.

I think these lemmas are important enough to deserve a `@[deprecated]` annotation.
Thanks for the suggestion.

```suggestion
    f = g := by
```
Do the `IsIso` variants of these lemmas already exist? If not, could you add them?
It does exist as `Functor.map_hom_inv`. I shall try to make them simp lemmas.
(Making them `simp` lemmas was not a good idea...)
It doesn't matter, but you're using both `⟨⟩` and `()` for products in this file. You could clean this up to aid readability slightly.

Would be great if we could get rid of this defeq abuse. We can still merge this, I just feel that every case where something like this is necessary makes the API a bit harder to learn, because you can no longer see all the required tools by studying the available lemmas, you also need to keep all of the definitions in your head.

If you are referring to the `rfl`, `dsimp` was also closing the goal. If you are referring to the `erw`, I did not manage to make a significant improvement. The end of the proof is now:
```lean
  simp only [← assoc]
  congr 2
  symm
  apply NatTrans.naturality_app (associator.hom.app (X₁ i₁))
```

I think this declares the deprecated name `CategoryTheory.Iso.map_hom_inv_app`, but it should be `CategoryTheory.map_hom_inv_app`.

```suggestion
end Iso

@[deprecated (since := "2024-05-27")] alias map_hom_inv_app := Iso.map_hom_inv_id_app
@[deprecated (since := "2024-05-27")] alias map_inv_hom_app := Iso.map_inv_hom_id_app
```

Also, you're missing the `_assoc` versions.
